.q1 Question:
.q2 In Ruby how do I write to a file?
.tags
  %span.tagtag Tags:
  %a.xtag(href='/tags/ruby') ruby
  %a.xtag(href='/tags/write') write
  %a.xtag(href='/tags/file') file
  %a.xtag(href='/tags/open') open
%br/
Let the syntax do the writing:

%pre
  %code.ruby
    mystring = 'hello world'
    fh = File.open('/tmp/hello.txt','w')
    fh.puts mystring
    fh.close
    p 'Do it another way'
    File.open('/tmp/bye.txt', 'w') do |fh2|
    fh2.puts 'bye now'
    end
